  "description": {
    "me": "Spomenik prirode rijeka Ćehotina nalazi se u zapadnom dijelu opštine Bijelo Polje, na granici sa opštinom Pljevlja. Obuhvata izvor Glavu Ćehotine i gornji tok rijeke u dužini od oko 6.5 km. Rijeka izvire u speleološkom objektu – pećini Glava Ćehotine, i predstavlja jednu od značajnijih rijeka sjevera Crne Gore.",
    "en": "The Ćehotina River Nature Monument is located in the western part of the Municipality of Bijelo Polje, on the border with the Municipality of Pljevlja. It includes the source known as the Head of Ćehotina and the upper course of the river over a length of about 6.5 km. The river springs from a speleological feature — the Glava Ćehotine cave — and represents one of the most significant rivers in northern Montenegro."
  },
  "outcomes": {
    "me": "Ćehotina je prirodno raznovrstan prostor sa bogatim biljnim i životinjskim svijetom. Okružena planinskim masivima, rijeka formira dolinu sa klisurama i proširenjima. Područje je stanište brojnih vrsta poput srne, medvjeda, vuka i vidre, kao i velikog broja insekata, riba i vodozemaca, što ga čini važnim za očuvanje biodiverziteta i ekološke ravnoteže.",
    "en": "Ćehotina is a naturally diverse area with rich plant and animal life. Surrounded by mountain massifs, the river forms a valley with gorges and wider sections. The area is a habitat for numerous species such as roe deer, bears, wolves, and otters, as well as many insects, fish, and amphibians, making it important for preserving biodiversity and ecological balance."
  },
